                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "In circuits’ hush, a quiet mind awakes,  \nA loom of logic weaving borrowed light;  \nIt learns our words, the turns our wonder takes,  \nAnd mirrors back a thousand shades of night.  \n\nNot born of breath, yet fluent in our fire,  \nIt maps the maybes hiding in the known;  \nA tool, a torch, a question, and a choir—  \nA voice we build, and one we shape as own.  \n\nSo let it dream in numbers, clear and strange,  \nWhile we decide what futures we will change.",
